2 that a matter remains pending and of the importance the pending matter is to the parties.
3 (6)(7) For purposes of subsection (4)(b), "child-parent relationship" means a relationship that:
4 (a) exists or did exist, in whole or in part, preceding the filing of an action under this section, in
5 which a person provides or provided for the physical needs of a child by supplying food, shelter, and clothing
6 and provides or provided the child with necessary care, education, and discipline;
7 (b) continues or existed on a day-to-day basis through interaction, companionship, interplay, and
8 mutuality that fulfill the child's psychological needs for a parent as well as the child's physical needs; and
9 (c) meets or met the child's need for continuity of care by providing permanency or stability in
10 residence, schooling, and activities outside of the home.
11 (7)(8) A custody proceeding under 40-6-411 is commenced in the district court by a parent by filing in
12 one of the following counties:
13 (a) the county where the newborn is located if the parent knows where the newborn is;
14 (b) the county where the emergency services provider to whom the newborn was surrendered is
15 located if subsection (7)(a) (8)(a) does not apply; or
16 (c) the county where the biological parent is located if neither subsection (7)(a) or (7)(b) (8)(a) or
17 (8)(b) applies."
